      "writtenOn": "2026-04-02T08:01:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for the feedback!. You\u0027re right that these are slots and the rename was the wrong approach.\n\nThe original motivation was to support multi-host power state monitoring in phosphor-pid-control([86857]). Given your point about topologies where the slot-to-host mapping is not one-to-one, would the right approach be to keep SlotId and introduce a separate HostId property alongside it as in [88869]? That way consuming services would use HostId for host power state lookups and SlotId for chassis power state lookups. This would also mean the host state handling in dbus-sensors [74073] needs an update to read HostId rather than SlotId.\n\nIf that sounds right, I\u0027ll abandon this change and activate [88869] with corresponding updates to [74073] and [86857].\n\n[74073]: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/74073\n[86857]: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-pid-control/+/86857\n[88869]: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/entity-manager/+/88869",
